00:01:06,199 --> 00:01:11,179
HOWL'S MOVING CASTLE

4
00:01:39,866 --> 00:01:40,686
Miss Sophie

5
00:01:41,668 --> 00:01:43,098
I've closed up the shop

6
00:01:43,403 --> 00:01:45,593
You should come too, Sophie

7
00:01:46,006 --> 00:01:48,666
I'll just finish this
Go have some fun

8
00:01:49,242 --> 00:01:50,942
All right, then. I'm off

9
00:01:52,079 --> 00:01:53,279
I'm going

10
00:01:54,414 --> 00:01:56,284
Look, it's Howl's castle

11
00:01:56,650 --> 00:01:57,910
What? Howl? Where, where?

12
00:01:58,185 --> 00:01:59,965
Look how close it is

13
00:02:00,754 --> 00:02:02,064
Oh, no

14
00:02:02,356 --> 00:02:04,106
l wonder if Howl's in town

15
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:13,366
It took off

16
00:02:13,567 --> 00:02:15,937
No, just hiding
from all the soldiers

17
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:18,650
Say. did you hear?
Remember Martha, from South Haven?

18
00:02:19,072 --> 00:02:21,212
They say Howl tore her heart out

19
00:02:21,608 --> 00:02:22,338
How scary...

20
00:02:22,542 --> 00:02:24,762
Don't worry, he's not going
to want yours

21
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:28,030
Hurry up

22
00:02:29,583 --> 00:02:31,253
Really?

23
00:02:31,918 --> 00:02:33,878
Oh, cut it out...

24
00:04:34,508 --> 00:04:36,878
Hey there little mouse,
lost your way?

25
00:04:37,577 --> 00:04:39,157
Oh, no... I'm fine

26
00:04:39,913 --> 00:04:41,663
Then how about a cup of tea?

27
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:43,135
Care to join me?

28
00:04:43,683 --> 00:04:44,823
No thank you, I'm busy

29
00:04:45,085 --> 00:04:47,455
She sure is a cute little mouse

30
00:04:47,888 --> 00:04:49,878
Say, how old are you?
You live around here?

31
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:51,871
Let me pass!

32
00:04:52,492 --> 00:04:55,122
See, it's those whiskers of yours

33
00:04:55,562 --> 00:04:57,797
She's even cuter when she's mad

34
00:04:58,031 --> 00:04:59,341
Hey, there, I'm sorry

35
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:01,746
Where' ve you been?

36
00:05:02,435 --> 00:05:03,165
Who are you?

37
00:05:03,370 --> 00:05:04,680
I'm with her

38
00:05:04,971 --> 00:05:07,491
Why don't you two take
a little walk

39
00:05:10,210 --> 00:05:13,169
What the...?
Hey, wha...

40
00:05:15,348 --> 00:05:16,638
Don't hold it against them

41
00:05:17,384 --> 00:05:18,904
They're harmless

42
00:05:19,219 --> 00:05:22,089
Where to? I'll be your escort

43
00:05:22,756 --> 00:05:24,806
No. really, I'm only going to Cesari's

44
00:05:25,525 --> 00:05:27,484
Act normal
I'm being followed

45
00:05:27,861 --> 00:05:28,941
Just walk

46
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:51,980
Sorry, 1 got you involved

47
00:05:56,389 --> 00:05:57,089
This way

48
00:06:05,065 --> 00:06:05,675
Hold on

49
00:06:11,805 --> 00:06:13,975
Drop your legs. keep walking

50
00:06:19,279 --> 00:06:21,649
That's right, don't be frightened

51
00:06:37,664 --> 00:06:38,804
Very nice

52
00:06:53,813 --> 00:06:55,483
I'll draw them off

53
00:06:55,815 --> 00:06:57,395
Wait here until the coast is clear

54
00:06:58,184 --> 00:06:59,054
Yes

55
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:01,190
That's my girl

56
00:07:14,134 --> 00:07:15,184
Any chocolate Letties?

57
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:16,775
Look this way, Lettie

58
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:17,860
Hey. make room

59
00:07:18,071 --> 00:07:19,031
Let's go for a walk, Lettie

60
00:07:19,272 --> 00:07:20,142
My sister?

61
00:07:21,641 --> 00:07:23,451
Come back soon, Lettie

62
00:07:27,547 --> 00:07:28,477
Sophie?

63
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:31,863
How did you land
on the veranda like that?

64
00:07:32,218 --> 00:07:33,478
Have you become an angel?

65
00:07:34,254 --> 00:07:36,504
It feels like I'm in a dream...

66
00:07:36,923 --> 00:07:38,853
Lettie, why not use the office?

67
00:07:39,259 --> 00:07:42,249
Thanks, but ! should really
be working

68
00:07:43,930 --> 00:07:47,000
What?
You sure he wasn't a wizard?

69
00:07:47,701 --> 00:07:49,281
He was so kind...

70
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:52,240
He rescued me...

71
00:07:52,605 --> 00:07:55,035
Don't tell me he's stolen your heart

72
00:07:56,076 --> 00:07:59,586
If that was the wizard Howl,
he'd have eaten it right up

73
00:08:00,714 --> 00:08:03,674
Don't worry,
Howl's only after beauties

74
00:08:04,451 --> 00:08:05,741
There you go again

75
00:08:06,019 --> 00:08:08,859
Listen to me,
we live in dangerous times

76
00:08:09,356 --> 00:08:11,936
They say even the Witch of the Waste
is back on the prowl

77
00:08:13,793 --> 00:08:15,193
Sophie?

78
00:08:16,763 --> 00:08:17,933
Oh, you...

79
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,570
Lettie, the Madeleines are done

80
00:08:23,470 --> 00:08:24,900
Okay, be right there

81
00:08:25,205 --> 00:08:26,344
All right

82
00:08:28,375 --> 00:08:29,715
I'm going home

83
00:08:30,010 --> 00:08:31,969
It's a relief to know
you're doing well

84
00:08:34,313 --> 00:08:35,164
Hello, Lettie

85
00:08:35,381 --> 00:08:36,431
Nice to see you

86
00:08:36,950 --> 00:08:40,110
Listen. are you going to spend
your whole life in that shop?

87
00:08:41,988 --> 00:08:45,148
It meant so much to Papa
Besides, I'm the eldest

88
00:08:45,692 --> 00:08:49,292
That's not what I meant
Are you sure you want to be a hatter?

89
00:08:50,263 --> 00:08:51,163
Well, I...

90
00:08:51,398 --> 00:08:52,508
Bye, Lettie

91
00:08:52,766 --> 00:08:53,966
Come by the shop next time

92
00:08:54,234 --> 00:08:55,054
Sure

93
00:08:55,268 --> 00:08:56,198
I'll be on my way

94
00:08:56,436 --> 00:08:59,806
Sophie. you've got to
look out for yourself

95
00:10:08,341 --> 00:10:10,271
Sorry, the shop's closed

96
00:10:10,643 --> 00:10:12,863
I thought I'd locked the door

97
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:19,608
What a cheap shop,
full of cheap little hats

98
00:10:21,254 --> 00:10:23,944
And you're quite cheap-looking yourself

99
00:10:25,758 --> 00:10:27,948
This is just a simple hat shop

100
00:10:34,601 --> 00:10:36,301
I think you had better leave

101
00:10:37,604 --> 00:10:40,624
You're very brave, taking on
the Witch of the Waste

102
00:10:41,541 --> 00:10:42,971
The Witch of the Waste?

103
00:10:50,850 --> 00:10:53,720
You won't be able to tell anyone
about that spell

104
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:56,330
My regards to Howl

105
00:11:43,069 --> 00:11:44,878
Is this really me!

106
00:11:45,238 --> 00:11:47,138
I've got to stay calm

107
00:12:04,023 --> 00:12:05,453
I've got to calm down

108
00:12:05,792 --> 00:12:08,312
It's no use panicking, Sophie

109
00:12:10,396 --> 00:12:12,536
I'll be fine, I'll be fine

110
00:12:14,534 --> 00:12:18,254
I've got to calm down

111
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:31,466
I'm back!

112
00:12:31,851 --> 00:12:32,991
Welcome home, Ma'am!

113
00:12:33,253 --> 00:12:34,623
- Welcome home
- How do you like it?

114
00:12:34,921 --> 00:12:36,561
It's all the rage in Kingsbury

115
00:12:36,889 --> 00:12:37,939
Amazing

116
00:12:38,191 --> 00:12:39,011
It suits you

117
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:41,129
Don't you think it's wonderful?

118
00:12:41,561 --> 00:12:42,381
Sophie!

119
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:46,906
Mrs. Hatter, Sophie hasn't come down
to work yet

120
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:49,069
Il wonder what's the matter?

121
00:12:51,638 --> 00:12:53,098
Sophie!

122
00:13:00,079 --> 00:13:01,689
Don't come in

123
00:13:02,015 --> 00:13:04,005
I've got an awful cold

124
00:13:04,384 --> 00:13:05,934
I don't want you to catch it

125
00:13:06,886 --> 00:13:08,636
You sound just awful...

126
00:13:08,988 --> 00:13:10,718
Like some 90 year-old woman

127
00:13:11,057 --> 00:13:13,487
I'll stay in bed today

128
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:16,330
You sure? All right, then

129
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:20,634
Here we go...

130
00:13:32,045 --> 00:13:33,685
You'll be fine, old lady

131
00:13:34,013 --> 00:13:37,673
You're still healthy. and these clothes
finally suit you

132
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:42,730
But I can't stay here

133
00:13:53,599 --> 00:13:54,589
Ouch, ouch

134
00:13:54,901 --> 00:13:57,560
It's not easy being old

135
00:14:07,413 --> 00:14:10,253
They're saying this war
is going to be terrible...

136
00:14:22,495 --> 00:14:24,335
Like a hand, granny?

137
00:14:24,964 --> 00:14:28,184
Such a gentleman,
but I'll manage

138
00:14:29,502 --> 00:14:32,021
Sure, old lady,
but where are you off to?

139
00:14:32,472 --> 00:14:34,752
Just a bit farther than where
you're going

140
00:14:39,779 --> 00:14:41,559
I don't recommend it, granny

141
00:14:41,914 --> 00:14:44,223
Nothing but witches and wizards ahead

142
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:46,290
Thank you

143
00:14:47,186 --> 00:14:49,206
Going to the Folding Valley,
at this hour?

144
00:14:49,589 --> 00:14:51,779
Says her youngest sister's there

145
00:15:06,439 --> 00:15:08,809
I've hardly made any progress at all

146
00:15:11,043 --> 00:15:13,913
Thank goodness I've still got my teeth

147
00:15:21,654 --> 00:15:23,464
That'll make a good cane

148
00:15:23,890 --> 00:15:25,590
Up we go

149
00:15:32,064 --> 00:15:34,113
Might be a bit too thick

150
00:15:43,009 --> 00:15:44,379
Ouch, ouch

151
00:15:45,511 --> 00:15:46,771
What a stubborn branch

152
00:15:49,415 --> 00:15:51,495
Never underestimate
Grandma Sophie

153
00:15:52,285 --> 00:15:53,454
Heave

154
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:08,154
A scarecrow, eh?! thought you were
working for the Witch

155
00:16:09,001 --> 00:16:11,611
But how do you stand by yourself?

156
00:16:14,574 --> 00:16:16,353
Your head's a turnip

157
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:19,936
I've always hated turnips

158
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,730
At least you're not
upside down anymore

159
00:16:23,216 --> 00:16:24,676
So long

160
00:16:32,091 --> 00:16:33,641
It's so cold

161
00:16:34,427 --> 00:16:36,387
The town's still so close

162
00:16:42,168 --> 00:16:46,208
Don't follow me
You don't owe me a thing

163
00:16:47,106 --> 00:16:48,886
You must be a magical whatever-you-are

164
00:16:49,242 --> 00:16:51,762
I've had enough of witches and spells!

165
00:16:52,678 --> 00:16:55,168
Just go stand wherever you like!

166
00:17:16,569 --> 00:17:19,589
This is a perfect cane
Thank you kindly

167
00:17:20,106 --> 00:17:23,886
While you're at it, could you bring me
a house to sleep in?

168
00:17:35,488 --> 00:17:37,918
Seems you get more cunning with age

169
00:17:49,135 --> 00:17:50,775
What a huge battleship

170
00:17:53,639 --> 00:17:57,329
I never realized how weak you feel
when you get old

171
00:18:14,293 --> 00:18:18,043
I smell smoke
Maybe there's a cabin

172
00:18:38,217 --> 00:18:40,617
Turnip-head, isn't that Howl's Castle?

173
00:18:41,387 --> 00:18:44,667
This is hardly what I meant
when I asked for shelter!

174
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:57,338
What is this?

175
00:18:57,637 --> 00:18:58,947
You call this a castle?

176
00:19:19,325 --> 00:19:21,165
Is that the way in?

177
00:19:23,329 --> 00:19:25,029
Just wait up there

178
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:28,866
Hey, there!

179
00:19:30,369 --> 00:19:32,799
Are you going to let me on, or not!

180
00:19:37,677 --> 00:19:39,256
My shawl!

181
00:19:52,558 --> 00:19:55,808
It seems warm enough inside, Turnip
I'm going in

182
00:19:56,362 --> 00:19:57,382
Thank you

183
00:19:57,630 --> 00:20:01,110
Even Howl wouldn't want
an ancient heart like mine

184
00:20:04,370 --> 00:20:05,889
This time, it's really goodbye

185
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:08,754
You may be a turnip,
but you're a good turnip

186
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:10,958
May you find happiness

187
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:02,157
What is this place?
Just looks like a dilapidated heap

188
00:21:11,337 --> 00:21:15,407
Well. one nice thing about getting old
is that nothing surprises you anymore

189
00:21:25,551 --> 00:21:27,511
That's some spell you're under

190
00:21:28,821 --> 00:21:31,400
It won't be easy to break

191
00:21:33,392 --> 00:21:34,622
The fire talked

192
00:21:34,927 --> 00:21:37,097
And you can't even
tell anyone about it

193
00:21:37,763 --> 00:21:39,193
You're Howl?

194
00:21:39,498 --> 00:21:43,508
Wrong. I'm the fire demon, Calcifer!

195
00:21:44,436 --> 00:21:48,275
Well. then, Calcifer, can you break
the spell I'm under?

196
00:21:49,441 --> 00:21:50,371
Easy

197
00:21:50,609 --> 00:21:52,829
If you break the spell that chains me
to this place,

198
00:21:53,245 --> 00:21:55,495
I'll break your spell in a flash

199
00:21:56,615 --> 00:21:59,015
In other words, bargain with a demon

200
00:21:59,552 --> 00:22:01,631
You sure you can keep that promise?

201
00:22:02,254 --> 00:22:04,303
Demons don't make promises

202
00:22:06,058 --> 00:22:07,488
I suggest you look elsewhere

203
00:22:07,893 --> 00:22:09,793
But I'm an exploited demon

204
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:13,262
I'm chained here by a contract with Howl,
who works me to death

205
00:22:13,833 --> 00:22:16,463
I'm the one who keeps
this castle moving

206
00:22:16,969 --> 00:22:20,099
My, you've got it rough

207
00:22:21,006 --> 00:22:24,606
If you figure out the secret contract.
the spell will break

208
00:22:25,211 --> 00:22:27,731
If you do that,
I'll break your spell, too

209
00:22:28,747 --> 00:22:32,147
All right
A bargain, eh?

210
00:22:37,957 --> 00:22:39,157
Granny

211
00:22:39,425 --> 00:22:40,625
Granny

212
00:22:45,464 --> 00:22:47,274
Boy...
I've got my doubts about her

213
00:23:41,787 --> 00:23:43,187
Hey, who's this?

214
00:23:43,489 --> 00:23:44,919
Porthaven!

215
00:23:45,324 --> 00:23:47,224
When did she get in?

216
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:55,756
Stand by

217
00:24:00,239 --> 00:24:01,699
Why. Mayor. sir

218
00:24:02,007 --> 00:24:05,517
The sun is already high
Is Master Jenkins at home?

219
00:24:06,345 --> 00:24:08,015
The Master is out

220
00:24:08,347 --> 00:24:10,687
l answer in his stead

221
00:24:11,650 --> 00:24:14,080
An invitation from His Majesty

222
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:15,690
It has come to war

223
00:24:16,188 --> 00:24:18,408
His Majesty desires every wizard

224
00:24:18,824 --> 00:24:21,404
and magician, even the witches,
to aid our homeland

225
00:24:21,860 --> 00:24:24,790
His presence is imperative
That is all

226
00:24:27,733 --> 00:24:29,283
War. how awful

227
00:24:30,336 --> 00:24:32,116
And who might you be?

228
00:24:32,938 --> 00:24:34,488
Calcifer let me in

229
00:24:34,807 --> 00:24:37,707
Don't look at me
She wandered in from the Wastes

230
00:24:38,477 --> 00:24:39,467
The Wastes?

231
00:24:39,712 --> 00:24:42,612
That's strange
You're not a witch, are you?

232
00:24:43,749 --> 00:24:45,649
A witch could never get in

233
00:24:46,452 --> 00:24:48,122
Porthaven, again

234
00:24:49,221 --> 00:24:50,451
A customer?

235
00:24:52,558 --> 00:24:53,988
Stand by

236
00:24:56,962 --> 00:24:58,392
State your purpose

237
00:24:58,697 --> 00:25:00,187
Mama sent me

238
00:25:00,799 --> 00:25:03,199
The usual spell?

239
00:25:04,837 --> 00:25:06,737
Behave yourself, now

240
00:25:23,956 --> 00:25:25,216
It's not the Wastes

241
00:25:25,491 --> 00:25:28,011
Granny, are you a witch, too?

242
00:25:28,927 --> 00:25:32,647
That's right,
I'm the scariest witch in the land

243
00:25:33,265 --> 00:25:35,875
Sprinkle this powder on your ship
and the winds will favor it

244
00:25:36,335 --> 00:25:37,355
Sure

245
00:25:39,805 --> 00:25:41,235
Many thanks

246
00:25:43,442 --> 00:25:45,462
l can't have you making up things

247
00:25:45,844 --> 00:25:47,514
You should give up that disguise

248
00:25:47,846 --> 00:25:50,426
It's not a disguise, it's magic

249
00:25:52,518 --> 00:25:54,128
The Kingsbury door

250
00:25:56,021 --> 00:25:56,921
Stand by

251
00:26:02,528 --> 00:26:04,958
Is this the residence of
Wizard Pendragon?

252
00:26:05,397 --> 00:26:06,387
It is, indeed

253
00:26:06,632 --> 00:26:09,442
l bear an invitation
from His Majesty

254
00:26:09,935 --> 00:26:13,885
Please inform Master Pendragon
that he is required at the Palace

255
00:26:15,140 --> 00:26:17,040
Our thanks to you

256
00:26:31,890 --> 00:26:34,230
A city fit for a king

257
00:26:34,660 --> 00:26:37,060
Get back in or you'll lose your nose

258
00:26:42,468 --> 00:26:44,518
Stop wandering around

259
00:27:20,806 --> 00:27:23,556
That's enough!
I'm going to get really mad

260
00:27:24,910 --> 00:27:26,720
This is a magic house, isn't it?

261
00:27:27,079 --> 00:27:27,899
Oh, boy!

262
00:27:28,113 --> 00:27:29,953
Where does the black one lead?

263
00:27:30,315 --> 00:27:31,545
Only Master Howl knows

264
00:27:32,417 --> 00:27:34,437
I'm having my breakfast

265
00:27:43,996 --> 00:27:46,076
But you've got bacon and eggs

266
00:27:47,266 --> 00:27:50,046
We can't use the fire
when Master Howl's away

267
00:27:53,939 --> 00:27:55,639
I'll cook for you

268
00:27:56,341 --> 00:27:57,210
But you can't

269
00:27:57,442 --> 00:28:00,402
Calcifer only obeys Master Howl

270
00:28:00,979 --> 00:28:03,319
That's right. l won't cook for you

271
00:28:03,749 --> 00:28:06,269
Oh, here's my hat

272
00:28:09,855 --> 00:28:12,405
All right, Calcifer
Be a good fire, now

273
00:28:13,025 --> 00:28:15,045
Forget it, I'm a demon

274
00:28:15,427 --> 00:28:17,766
l answer to no one

275
