taken a liking to me

389
00:38:00,411 --> 00:38:02,111
He followed me here

390
00:38:02,447 --> 00:38:04,437
Are you sure you're not a witch, Sophie?

391
00:38:04,816 --> 00:38:08,035
That's right, I'm the cleanest witch
in the land

392
00:38:37,715 --> 00:38:40,235
Turnip, don't pull it so tight

393
00:38:49,694 --> 00:38:51,944
Seems like he likes doing the wash

394
00:38:52,363 --> 00:38:54,383
They'll dry in no time

395
00:38:57,101 --> 00:38:59,181
Turnip must belong to the demons

396
00:38:59,571 --> 00:39:01,060
Calcifer doesn't seem to mind him

397
00:39:01,372 --> 00:39:04,002
You're right,
maybe he's a demon of the dead

398
00:39:05,543 --> 00:39:08,703
But he led me
to this wonderful place

399
00:39:51,489 --> 00:39:53,949
I've put away all the laundry, Sophie

400
00:39:54,459 --> 00:39:57,479
Why, thank you
We'd better be getting back

401
00:39:58,129 --> 00:39:59,799
How mysterious

402
00:40:00,131 --> 00:40:03,151
I've never felt such peace

403
00:41:22,246 --> 00:41:23,296
Stinks

404
00:41:23,648 --> 00:41:25,988
You reek of burnt flesh and steel

405
00:41:45,970 --> 00:41:48,689
Keep flying and one day you
won't be able to change yourself back

406
00:41:53,578 --> 00:41:55,858
Isn't it great! Sophie did this for me

407
00:41:59,317 --> 00:42:00,927
The fighting is fierce

408
00:42:01,252 --> 00:42:04,502
The country's ablaze, from the
southern coast to the northern border

409
00:42:05,490 --> 00:42:07,479
Il hate the fire in gunpowder

410
00:42:07,859 --> 00:42:10,229
They have no manners

411
00:42:11,696 --> 00:42:12,986
My own kind attacked me

412
00:42:13,264 --> 00:42:14,554
The Witch of the Waste?

413
00:42:14,832 --> 00:42:17,872
Hack wizards masquerading
as monsters

414
00:42:18,870 --> 00:42:21,500
They'll cry plenty later on,

415
00:42:21,973 --> 00:42:23,873
when they can't regain human form

416
00:42:24,642 --> 00:42:27,422
No. they'll just forget
they ever knew how to cry

417
00:42:27,912 --> 00:42:30,252
Aren't you supposed to report
to the king yourself?

418
00:42:30,681 --> 00:42:31,851
Yes, well...

419
00:42:32,116 --> 00:42:33,486
Hot water for my bath

420
00:42:33,785 --> 00:42:35,395
Oh, no, not again

421
00:43:08,653 --> 00:43:09,732
Is that Howl?

422
00:43:09,987 --> 00:43:12,007
Yeah, wasting my hot water again

423
00:43:17,895 --> 00:43:20,205
I'm sure Howl won't eat any breakfast

424
00:43:20,631 --> 00:43:21,531
No matter

425
00:43:21,766 --> 00:43:23,166
Morning

426
00:43:26,437 --> 00:43:28,187
It's lovely shopping in the morning

427
00:43:28,539 --> 00:43:30,209
I've never seen the ocean

428
00:43:31,275 --> 00:43:32,915
Such beautiful, sparkling water

429
00:43:33,244 --> 00:43:35,024
Same as it always is

430
00:43:44,589 --> 00:43:46,259
I myself hate potatoes

431
00:43:46,591 --> 00:43:47,580
Pay up

432
00:43:47,825 --> 00:43:49,055
Thank you

433
00:43:49,527 --> 00:43:50,347
Thanks

434
00:43:52,330 --> 00:43:54,520
Fish, all fresh off the boat

435
00:43:55,166 --> 00:43:56,036
That one's tasty

436
00:43:56,267 --> 00:43:58,437
I myself hate fish

437
00:43:59,003 --> 00:44:00,843
The fleet's come home

438
00:44:01,205 --> 00:44:02,075
Is that the smoke?

439
00:44:02,306 --> 00:44:03,916
There's been another battle

440
00:44:04,275 --> 00:44:06,005
Really? Sorry. lady, later

441
00:44:06,344 --> 00:44:07,774
That ship's on fire!

442
00:44:31,335 --> 00:44:33,065
Sophie. let's go get a closer look

443
00:44:33,404 --> 00:44:36,094
No, I've no stomach for such things
Let's go home

444
00:44:37,241 --> 00:44:39,551
Our most advanced battleship.
reduced to this

445
00:44:44,582 --> 00:44:46,511
