I've become a cleaning lady

547
00:54:27,131 --> 00:54:28,741
My how delightful

548
00:54:29,833 --> 00:54:32,793
By the way. what brings you
to see the king?

549
00:54:33,303 --> 00:54:36,343
Job hunting
I'm sick of working for Howl

550
00:54:36,874 --> 00:54:37,834
And yourself?

551
00:54:38,609 --> 00:54:40,919
The king invited me

552
00:54:41,378 --> 00:54:45,418
It seems that idiot. Suliman,
finally needs my power

553
00:54:46,316 --> 00:54:49,216
Why don't you break the spell
you put on me

554
00:54:49,987 --> 00:54:51,387
That's impossible

555
00:54:51,688 --> 00:54:55,228
My gifts lie in casting spells,
not breaking them

556
00:54:55,826 --> 00:54:57,996
See you later, then

557
00:54:58,662 --> 00:55:01,732
Hey, wait a minute
dust wait!

558
00:55:03,400 --> 00:55:05,710
If you weren't here,
I'd have hit her with my cane

559
00:55:23,987 --> 00:55:25,354
What's wrong with you?

560
00:55:25,556 --> 00:55:28,596
Madam, vehicles are prohibited
beyond this point

561
00:55:29,126 --> 00:55:30,526
Please continue on foot

562
00:55:31,195 --> 00:55:32,485
That Suliman

563
00:55:32,763 --> 00:55:36,243
Using magic to force me
to climb these stairs

564
00:55:47,578 --> 00:55:49,798
We'll catch up
Pay her no mind

565
00:56:15,272 --> 00:56:17,932
Heavy. why are you so heavy?

566
00:56:28,218 --> 00:56:31,647
You... Hey... Wait

567
00:56:32,389 --> 00:56:33,649
What is it?

568
00:56:33,924 --> 00:56:37,614
Suddenly remembered...
how to break my spell?

569
00:56:38,228 --> 00:56:41,478
I told you...

570
00:56:42,132 --> 00:56:43,002
I don't know how

571
00:56:43,367 --> 00:56:45,037
Then, start studying up

572
00:56:49,973 --> 00:56:51,843
I don't get it

573
00:56:52,209 --> 00:56:55,019
Where does she get all that energy?

574
00:57:03,587 --> 00:57:05,287
I have to put you down

575
00:57:11,862 --> 00:57:15,202
Why don't you call it a day?
You can't make it

576
00:57:16,266 --> 00:57:20,576
It's been 50 years now,
since they drove me out of here...

577
00:57:21,438 --> 00:57:25,718
I've been longing for this day...
Ever since

578
00:57:26,476 --> 00:57:28,026
Good luck to you. then

579
00:57:28,345 --> 00:57:31,154
Still. I'm not nice enough
to help you out

580
00:57:32,149 --> 00:57:33,519
Come, Howl

581
00:57:34,918 --> 00:57:36,668
You heartless wench

582
00:57:37,020 --> 00:57:39,360
Next time I'll turn you feeble, too

583
00:58:00,610 --> 00:58:02,450
Hurry up!

584
00:58:03,513 --> 00:58:05,473
Madam, follow me

585
00:58:06,016 --> 00:58:08,706
First. you should help her

586
00:58:09,186 --> 00:58:11,816
We are forbidden to assist anyone

587
00:58:12,322 --> 00:58:15,102
But the king himself invited her

588
00:58:15,592 --> 00:58:17,702
Hang in there!

589
00:58:18,762 --> 00:58:20,342
Just a little farther

590
00:58:21,365 --> 00:58:23,475
And you call yourself a witch?

591
00:58:25,002 --> 00:58:26,612
Who asked you?

592
00:58:29,406 --> 00:58:31,136
You suddenly look older

593
00:58:32,476 --> 00:58:35,286
Madam Pendragon and
the Witch of the Waste!

594
00:58:37,147 --> 00:58:38,547
Pull yourself together

595
00:58:38,849 --> 00:58:40,959
Isn't this what you've been waiting for?

596
00:58:44,421 --> 00:58:47,381
Madam Pendragon and
the Witch of the Waste!

597
00:58:47,891 --> 00:58:51,521
Pendragon...
That name sounds familiar

598
00:58:52,129 --> 00:58:55,288
Of course it does
That was the name of my hat shop

599
00:58:55,832 --> 00:58:56,792
It was?

600
00:58:57,467 --> 00:58:59,047
Please wait here

601
00:59:05,709 --> 00:59:06,729
A chair!

602
00:59:07,177 --> 00:59:08,637
It's mine!

603
00:59:20,657 --> 00:59:22,467
Howl, get back here

604
00:59:30,867 --> 00:59:32,297
Madam, this way please

605
01:00:32,896 --> 01:00:34,736
l understand you're Howl's mother

606
01:00:35,932 --> 01:00:37,741
Yes
My name is Pendragon

607
01:00:38,602 --> 01:00:40,712
I'm sure you're weary
Please have a seat

608
01:00:41,505 --> 01:00:42,495
Yes

609
01:00:52,516 --> 01:00:55,556
lam Madam Suliman, His Majesty's witch

610
01:01:02,125 --> 01:01:03,355
Um, that dog is...

611
01:01:04,227 --> 01:01:05,517
Ah. you mean Heen?

612
01:01:05,795 --> 01:01:08,925
He does my errands
l asked him to escort you

613
01:01:13,603 --> 01:01:15,593
Howl won't join us, then?

614
01:01:17,474 --> 01:01:20,084
You see, he sends his mother
to make excuses

615
01:01:20,544 --> 01:01:23,033
I'm sure he'd be utterly useless
to His Majesty

616
01:01:24,614 --> 01:01:26,834
What a shame

617
01:01:27,284 --> 01:01:30,064
He was my last apprentice...

618
01:01:31,421 --> 01:01:34,231
A student of such marvelous gifts

619
01:01:34,824 --> 01:01:38,304
I rejoiced in finally finding
a worthy heir

620
01:01:40,997 --> 01:01:43,926
But then, a demon stole his heart,

621
01:01:44,434 --> 01:01:46,334
and he abandoned me

622
01:01:46,703 --> 01:01:50,453
He turned his magic
to purely selfish uses

623
01:01:53,176 --> 01:01:54,466
Mrs. Pendragon

624
01:01:54,911 --> 01:01:56,641
That boy is dangerous

625
01:01:56,980 --> 01:02:00,640
His power is too great
for one with no heart

626
01:02:02,319 --> 01:02:06,069
If he follows that path he'll wind up
like the Witch of the Waste

627
01:02:06,690 --> 01:02:07,300
Bring her

628
01:02:13,997 --> 01:02:15,426
What happened?

629
01:02:17,734 --> 01:02:20,364
I just restored her to her real age

630
01:02:20,837 --> 01:02:22,357
All her powers are gone

631
01:02:23,039 --> 01:02:26,579
Once upon a time,
she was a magnificent witch

632
01:02:27,577 --> 01:02:29,947
She made a bargain with a demon

633
01:02:30,380 --> 01:02:33,280
who consumed her, body and soul,
long, long ago

634
01:02:34,084 --> 01:02:37,214
Our kingdom can no longer afford
to turn a blind eve

635
01:02:37,754 --> 01:02:39,564
to disreputable wizards and witches

636
01:02:39,923 --> 01:02:42,912
If Howl comes here
to serve the kingdom,

637
01:02:43,426 --> 01:02:45,976
I will teach him how to break
with the demon

638
01:02:46,730 --> 01:02:50,130
If not. I'll strip him of his powers
as l have taken hers

639
01:02:51,768 --> 01:02:52,668
Now just a minute

640
01:02:54,404 --> 01:02:57,064
Now [ understand why Howl
refused to come here

641
01:02:57,974 --> 01:02:59,264
Something's not right

642
01:02:59,542 --> 01:03:03,352
Forcing your aged guests to climb
stairs. dragging them into strange rooms

643
01:03:03,980 --> 01:03:05,150
It's like a trap

644
01:03:05,682 --> 01:03:07,412
You call Howl heartless!

645
01:03:07,751 --> 01:03:11,561
Yes, he's selfish and cowardly
and unpredictable

646
01:03:12,188 --> 01:03:14,968
But he's straight as an arrow
He only wants to be free

647
01:03:15,825 --> 01:03:18,225
Howl won't turn into an evil monster

648
01:03:18,662 --> 01:03:21,091
He'll battle the demon on his own

649
01:03:21,531 --> 01:03:23,141
I believe in him

650
01:03:23,933 --> 01:03:26,303
Mrs. Pendragon...
You're in love with Howl

651
01:03:27,504 --> 01:03:30,163
Howl...
Howl's coming?

652
01:03:30,774 --> 01:03:33,554
l want Howl's heart, ! want it

653
01:03:34,044 --> 01:03:37,234
That's enough from you
Howl's not coming

654
01:03:39,282 --> 01:03:41,062
Howl will most certainly come

655
01:03:42,285 --> 01:03:44,535
Now, I've found his weakness

656
01:03:51,594 --> 01:03:52,524
Your Majesty

657
01:03:52,762 --> 01:03:54,162
As you are

658
01:03:54,464 --> 01:03:55,804
How are you feeling?

659
01:03:56,099 --> 01:03:57,239
Thank you for asking

660
01:03:57,500 --> 01:04:00,490
Meetings bore me
flew out for a breather

661
01:04:01,571 --> 01:04:02,621
How lovely

662
01:04:02,939 --> 01:04:04,308
These are?

663
01:04:04,774 --> 01:04:06,854
This is Wizard Howl's mother

664
01:04:07,243 --> 01:04:08,442
I see

665
01:04:12,515 --> 01:04:16,495
l appreciate it. but] don't intend
to win any war with magic

666
01:04:17,754 --> 01:04:21,703
It's true that Suliman's powers
shield our palace from bombs

667
01:04:22,359 --> 01:04:24,609
But they just fall on neighboring towns

668
01:04:25,028 --> 01:04:27,308
That's how magic works
Right, Suliman?

669
01:04:27,731 --> 01:04:29,631
Such eloquence today, Your Majesty

670
01:04:30,133 --> 01:04:31,423
Suliman!

671
01:04:34,571 --> 01:04:38,051
This is the final battle
This time, we'll beat them to a pulp

672
01:04:41,511 --> 01:04:45,171
Suliman, you've outdone yourself
with that double. Await good news

673
01:04:45,782 --> 01:04:46,922
Thank you kindly

674
01:04:47,817 --> 01:04:49,397
Have my generals assembled?

675
01:04:53,623 --> 01:04:56,113
It's been awhile, Howl

676
01:04:56,559 --> 01:04:58,459
Delighted to see you doing so well

677
01:04:58,828 --> 01:05:00,698
l saw right through you

678
01:05:01,064 --> 01:05:02,703
I've kept my oath

679
01:05:03,333 --> 01:05:05,503
I've no wish to fight you

680
01:05:06,002 --> 01:05:07,292
I'll take my mother

681
01:05:07,604 --> 01:05:09,214
won't let you go

682
01:05:30,927 --> 01:05:32,767
Don't look down,
you'll be dragged down

683
01:05:33,630 --> 01:05:37,030
It's time 1 showed your mother
what you really are

684
01:06:31,788 --> 01:06:33,338
Howl, don't! It's a trap

685
01:06:46,769 --> 01:06:47,758
Hold tight

686
01:06:55,712 --> 01:06:57,202
Sophie. sit up front

687
01:06:59,115 --> 01:07:02,595
Oh, no. Sophie,
you brought the whole gang along

688
01:07:04,387 --> 01:07:05,527
Nice doggie

689
01:07:06,289 --> 01:07:09,039
You're just Suliman's spy

690
01:07:09,526 --> 01:07:11,895
Oh, well, too late to toss you now

691
01:07:12,328 --> 01:07:13,668
Sophie. you steer

692
01:07:13,963 --> 01:07:16,103
What! I can't possibly!

693
01:07:16,499 --> 01:07:17,839
They're after us

694
01:07:23,039 --> 01:07:25,939
I'll tackle them. Fly straight
to the castle in the Wastes

695
01:07:26,442 --> 01:07:28,052
What! That's impossible!

696
01:07:28,378 --> 01:07:31,098
Don't worry, the ring will guide you

697
01:07:31,581 --> 01:07:33,571
Summon Calcifer with your heart

698
01:07:33,950 --> 01:07:35,319
Summon Calcifer?

699
01:07:38,855 --> 01:07:39,815
It's glowing

700
01:07:41,357 --> 01:07:43,967
Follow the light
You'll be there by nightfall

701
01:07:44,460 --> 01:07:47,530
Why send me to Suliman
if you were coming yourself?

702
01:07:48,064 --> 01:07:50,234
Your presence gave me
the courage for it

703
01:07:50,633 --> 01:07:52,772
She's too terrible to
face on my own

704
01:07:53,670 --> 01:07:57,180
You've saved me
l was in grave danger back there

705
01:07:59,676 --> 01:08:01,016
Don't let go!

706
01:08:07,817 --> 01:08:09,307
- You're good
- Stop joking!

707
01:08:11,988 --> 01:08:13,477
We've got a lead now

708
01:08:14,057 --> 01:08:16,517
l can give you 5 minutes of invisibility,
now's your chance

709
01:08:20,430 --> 01:08:21,690
Howl!

710
01:08:34,109 --> 01:08:35,719
No, thank you

711
01:08:36,379 --> 01:08:39,448
Thank you. That's the most fun
I've had in ages

712
01:08:40,316 --> 01:08:42,946
I supposed Howl thinks
he's escaped...

713
01:08:43,685 --> 01:08:46,055
His mother's awfully young

714
01:09:37,240 --> 01:09:39,229
We're not far
That's my hometown

715
01:09:43,212 --> 01:09:45,992
Don't look so friendly
I don't trust you

716
01:10:10,406 --> 01:10:12,135
The castle
They've come to meet us

717
01:10:17,113 --> 01:10:19,103
Sophie!

718
01:10:19,716 --> 01:10:21,176
Markl, help!

719
01:10:21,484 --> 01:10:23,154
don't know how to stop this thing!

720
01:10:35,798 --> 01:10:37,058
Sophie!

721
01:10:38,134 --> 01:10:39,474
Doggie

722
01:10:41,671 --> 01:10:42,541
Markl

723
01:10:43,639 --> 01:10:44,809
I'm home

724
01:10:45,208 --> 01:10:46,987
Sophie, are you hurt?

725
01:10:48,344 --> 01:10:49,194
You're home!

726
01:10:49,412 --> 01:10:51,992
Thank you for coming to meet us

727
01:11:21,911 --> 01:11:25,071
Oh, no, you've gone too far

728
01:11:44,200 --> 01:11:45,950
l wonder if Howl's back

729
01:12:40,723 --> 01:12:41,743
Howl?

730
01:13:44,420 --> 01:13:45,910
Howl? Is it you?

731
01:13:49,558 --> 01:13:51,258
Are you hurt? In pain?

732
01:13:52,561 --> 01:13:54,260
Stay away

733
01:13:54,697 --> 01:13:56,477
l want to help you

734
01:13:56,832 --> 01:13:58,582
I want to break the spell you're under

735
01:14:00,002 --> 01:14:02,932
You can't even break your own spell

736
01:14:03,673 --> 01:14:05,572
But I love you!

737
01:14:06,142 --> 01:14:07,812
Too late

738
01:14:12,148 --> 01:14:13,318
Howl!

739
01:14:26,629 --> 01:14:28,059
Howl must be back

740
01:14:28,364 --> 01:14:32,313
Sophie. you'd better figure out
how to break my spell quick

741
01:14:33,336 --> 01:14:35,206
We're both running out of time

742
01:14:35,671 --> 01:14:38,071
Meaning Howl will turn into
a monster? Is it true?

743
01:14:38,507 --> 01:14:41,637
l can't tell you that
I'm a demon

744
01:14:43,913 --> 01:14:45,933
Calcifer, Suliman told me,

745
01:14:46,315 --> 01:14:48,945
Howl has given you
something very precious

746
01:14:49,418 --> 01:14:51,088
What is it?
Where is it?

747
01:14:51,420 --> 01:14:53,910
That's confidential information

748
01:14:54,357 --> 01:14:56,577
And if ] threaten
to dump water over you?

749
01:14:56,993 --> 01:14:59,393
How dare you!
Howl will die with me

750
01:15:19,615 --> 01:15:20,955
Good morning. Turnip

751
01:15:21,250 --> 01:15:23,351
We've got to be brave

752
01:15:26,489 --> 01:15:28,358
Ready. Sophie!

753
01:15:28,791 --> 01:15:31,721
OK! Open wider, Calcifer

754
01:15:33,162 --> 01:15:35,972
Here goes! Push!

755
01:15:36,465 --> 01:15:37,895
Heave!

756
01:15:45,975 --> 01:15:50,135
I... said... move!

757
01:15:50,880 --> 01:15:52,110
Come on!

758
01:16:14,070 --> 01:16:17,530
They call it a castle, but once
you get inside, it's a junk heap

759
01:16:20,276 --> 01:16:22,326
It's time to eat!

760
01:16:28,918 --> 01:16:30,378
Here, old girl

761
01:16:31,387 --> 01:16:34,257
But. Sophie
she's the Witch of the Waste

762
01:16:34,757 --> 01:16:36,067
No need to worry

763
01:16:36,358 --> 01:16:38,228
Why's she staring at me?

764
01:16:38,727 --> 01:16:40,777
Such a pretty fire

765
01:16:43,966 --> 01:16:44,816
Howl

766
01:16:45,034 --> 01:16:46,023
Hello, everyone

767
01:16:46,268 --> 01:16:47,138
Welcome home

768
01:16:47,369 --> 01:16:49,268
Master Howl,
can we keep this puppy?

769
01:16:50,139 --> 01:16:52,749
An old Witch and
Madam Suliman's dog

770
01:16:53,209 --> 01:16:55,259
Why'd you let them in, Calcifer?

771
01:16:56,078 --> 01:16:59,358
Don't look at me!
They blew in with Sophie

772
01:17:02,685 --> 01:17:04,265
Sophie. always dramatic...

773
01:17:04,920 --> 01:17:07,110
So you're Turnip

774
01:17:09,758 --> 01:17:11,718
You're under quite a spell, too

775
01:17:12,795 --> 01:17:14,815
Seems everyone in our little family
is complicated...

776
01:17:15,197 --> 01:17:17,127
He's so handsome

777
01:17:18,033 --> 01:17:20,693
This is a busy day
We're moving

778
01:17:21,337 --> 01:17:22,157
Moving?

779
01:17:22,371 --> 01:17:25,181
Oh, good. There aren't any shops,
here in the middle of nowhere

780
01:17:26,075 --> 01:17:29,035
Madam Suliman can track us down
in no time, here

781
01:17:29,712 --> 01:17:33,342
But you'll have to stay behind
The magic in your spell's too risky

782
01:17:39,922 --> 01:17:41,321
All right, that's done

783
01:17:42,091 --> 01:17:44,051
Take it away. Calcifer

784
01:17:59,275 --> 01:18:00,764
Excellent

785
01:18:01,076 --> 01:18:02,476
Stay right where you are

786
01:18:06,081 --> 01:18:07,781
Be gentle...

787
01:18:11,520 --> 01:18:12,540
Here goes

788
01:18:57,132 --> 01:18:59,621
We've moved
You can get up now

789
01:19:02,171 --> 01:19:04,131
Amazing, Master
It's so grand

790
01:19:05,007 --> 01:19:07,317
What a pretty fire

791
01:19:21,690 --> 01:19:23,000
This is...

792
01:19:23,292 --> 01:19:26,362
l added a bathroom
For our growing family

793
01:19:27,096 --> 01:19:30,165
Sophie, come here!
Sophie!

794
01:19:33,402 --> 01:19:36,092
l added a bedroom, too
Go in

795
01:19:46,949 --> 01:19:48,469
This is... why?

796
01:19:48,951 --> 01:19:51,731
I thought it would suit you
Do you like it?

797
01:19:53,555 --> 01:19:56,485
Yes, it's perfect
for a housekeeper

798
01:19:57,026 --> 01:19:59,635
I got you new clothes, too
Open them later. Next

799
01:20:00,863 --> 01:20:03,233
Sophie! Come here!
Quick!

800
01:20:04,433 --> 01:20:05,723
A courtyard!

801
01:20:06,001 --> 01:20:07,311
There's a shop, too

802
01:20:08,170 --> 01:20:09,630
Let's go, Heen!

803
01:20:10,506 --> 01:20:13,316
See that new color on the dial?
There's a new exit

804
01:20:17,012 --> 01:20:19,501
My gift to you. Sophie
Step outside

805
01:20:45,140 --> 01:20:46,920
It's my secret garden

806
01:20:47,743 --> 01:20:49,113
Beautiful

807
01:20:51,613 --> 01:20:53,633
Did you make it with your magic?

808
01:20:54,249 --> 01:20:56,769
Only a little, to help the flowers

809
01:21:06,228 --> 01:21:08,448
Thank you, Howl!

810
01:21:08,864 --> 01:21:10,204
It's like I'm dreaming

811
01:21:33,355 --> 01:21:34,434
Sophie

812
01:21:35,958 --> 01:21:39,968
How mysterious
I feel I've been here before

813
01:21:40,629 --> 01:21:42,358
l could cry with happiness

814
01:21:42,865 --> 01:21:43,885
Come

815
01:21:52,341 --> 01:21:53,331
Look

816
01:21:58,947 --> 01:22:00,257
A sweet little house

817
01:22:00,549 --> 01:22:02,249
My favorite hideaway

818
01:22:03,085 --> 01:22:06,335
When I was little I spent
my summers there alone

819
01:22:08,323 --> 01:22:09,583
Alone?

820
01:22:10,292 --> 01:22:13,602
My Uncle, the Wizard,
left it to me in secret

821
01:22:14,396 --> 01:22:16,585
Make yourself at home there, Sophie

822
01:22:20,736 --> 01:22:21,635
What's wrong?

823
01:22:22,438 --> 01:22:23,368
I'm scared

824
01:22:23,605 --> 01:22:26,264
I'm afraid you'll go off and disappear
somewhere, once I'm inside

825
01:22:29,378 --> 01:22:31,338
Howl, tell me the truth

826
01:22:31,713 --> 01:22:34,293
I don't mind if you're a monster

827
01:22:40,255 --> 01:22:43,445
l want to make sure that
you'll all live comfortably

828
01:22:44,193 --> 01:22:47,883
Why not a flower shop,
with all these flowers?

829
01:22:48,664 --> 01:22:50,744
You'd be good at it. Sophie

830
01:22:51,266 --> 01:22:53,106
And then. you'd go away?

831
01:22:55,204 --> 01:22:57,864
Il want to help you, Howl

832
01:22:58,574 --> 01:23:01,943
I'm not beautiful
and I'm only good at cleaning...

833
01:23:02,811 --> 01:23:05,121
Sophie, you are beautiful

834
01:23:09,518 --> 01:23:12,768
The good thing about being old
is that you've so little to lose...

835
01:23:26,835 --> 01:23:28,475
Why's that flying here?

836
01:23:28,804 --> 01:23:29,564
A battleship?

837
01:23:29,771 --> 01:23:31,141
On its way to burn cities and people

838
01:23:31,773 --> 01:23:32,823
The enemy's? Ours?

839
01:23:33,075 --> 01:23:34,825
What difference does it make?

840
01:23:47,623 --> 01:23:48,702
Murderers

841
01:23:56,365 --> 01:23:58,855
Look at all those bombs

842
01:24:15,217 --> 01:24:16,297
It stopped

843
01:24:16,552 --> 01:24:17,951
Did you do that?

844
01:24:18,253 --> 01:24:20,532
I'm just tinkering
It won't crash

845
01:24:24,359 --> 01:24:25,119
Howl!

846
01:24:25,427 --> 01:24:27,677
Oops, looks like they're onto us

847
01:24:37,639 --> 01:24:40,359
Madam Suliman's deputies
Let's go back

848
01:24:40,842 --> 01:24:42,802
Run! Move those legs

849
01:24:57,259 --> 01:24:58,339
Hurry on in!

850
01:24:58,594 --> 01:25:00,264
No! Don't let go!

851
01:25:09,905 --> 01:25:11,335
What happened. Sophie?

852
01:25:12,774 --> 01:25:14,264
I've had it with this place!

853
01:25:24,353 --> 01:25:25,993
Good night, Sophie

854
01:25:26,321 --> 01:25:27,461
Good night

855
01:25:29,524 --> 01:25:33,564
Don't worry about Master Howl, Sophie
Sometimes, he's gone for days on end

856
01:25:35,030 --> 01:25:36,429
Thank you, Markl

857
01:25:36,932 --> 01:25:37,802
Need the toilet?

858
01:25:38,033 --> 01:25:39,233
I'm fine

859
01:25:39,501 --> 01:25:40,991
Good night

860
01:25:41,770 --> 01:25:42,620
You're in love

861
01:25:45,674 --> 01:25:48,604
Sighing away like that

862
01:26:00,722 --> 01:26:02,242
I thought so

863
01:26:02,691 --> 01:26:04,741
Were you ever in love?

864
01:26:05,127 --> 01:26:07,707
Of course ! was
I'm still in love

865
01:26:08,163 --> 01:26:09,093
What?

866
01:26:09,598 --> 01:26:12,468
Men. why ever should we want them...

867
01:26:12,968 --> 01:26:14,958
But a young man's heart is so delicious!

868
01:26:15,737 --> 01:26:17,047
Unbelievable

869
01:26:17,673 --> 01:26:19,923
And so adorable, too

870
01:26:23,612 --> 01:26:24,922
What is that?

871
01:26:25,213 --> 01:26:26,383
Air raid siren

872
01:26:27,549 --> 01:26:28,339
Air raid?

873
01:26:29,851 --> 01:26:33,451
It's not for here
But best not go out tonight

874
01:26:35,457 --> 01:26:39,497
Suliman's creatures are searching
high and low for our house

875
01:26:42,964 --> 01:26:46,564
What a good fire,
hiding us so well

876
01:27:22,370 --> 01:27:24,480
Sophie. a stranger got in!

877
01:27:32,347 --> 01:27:33,217
Mother

878
01:27:33,648 --> 01:27:35,518
Sophie!

879
01:27:38,019 --> 01:27:40,679
Where have you been!
l searched for you everywhere!

880
01:27:41,423 --> 01:27:43,763
But, oh, look how you've aged!

881
01:27:44,593 --> 01:27:46,433
It's all my fault

882
01:27:48,497 --> 01:27:50,747
I'm so sorry, Sophie!

883
01:27:51,733 --> 01:27:53,023
Mother...

884
01:27:55,637 --> 01:27:57,687
l barely recognize the house

885
01:27:58,106 --> 01:27:59,656
Who is that?

886
01:27:59,975 --> 01:28:01,755
Oh, your landlady

887
01:28:02,144 --> 01:28:04,954
Sophie. I've got a new husband!

888
01:28:05,680 --> 01:28:08,110
He's such a wonderful man
And he's rich, too!

889
01:28:08,550 --> 01:28:09,980
We can all live together again

890
01:28:10,452 --> 01:28:12,642
You'll never have to clean again

891
01:28:13,522 --> 01:28:16,272
But I'm happy here...

892
01:28:16,758 --> 01:28:18,098
Really?

893
01:28:18,393 --> 01:28:19,323
Oops, ! forgot

894
01:28:19,628 --> 01:28:21,998
My car's waiting
I've got to run

895
01:28:26,568 --> 01:28:29,668
I'm so glad ! found you again

896
01:28:30,205 --> 01:28:32,015
We'll really catch up next time

897
01:28:32,374 --> 01:28:34,364
In the meantime, you take care

898
01:28:40,248 --> 01:28:43,848
A peeping-bug, eh?
The oldest trick in the book, Suliman

899
01:28:44,452 --> 01:28:45,852
All yours, Cal

900
01:28:55,564 --> 01:28:57,644
May you find happiness, Mother

901
01:28:58,033 --> 01:29:00,343
Thank you
You too, Sophie

902
01:29:04,673 --> 01:29:07,513
I've done what I was told
Take me back to my husband

903
01:29:08,009 --> 01:29:10,589
Yes. I'm sure Madam Suliman
will be pleased

904
01:29:13,114 --> 01:29:14,723
Forgive me, Sophie...

905
01:29:18,954 --> 01:29:20,244
Look at all these people

906
01:29:21,056 --> 01:29:23,955
They're all running away
The town will be empty

907
01:29:24,459 --> 01:29:26,449
Do you wish to run, too?

908
01:29:27,762 --> 01:29:29,661
That's what that lady spoke of...

909
01:29:30,332 --> 01:29:33,292
So, she did
I'm glad we made up

910
01:29:33,969 --> 01:29:35,699
Don't go, Sophie!

911
01:29:36,905 --> 01:29:39,804
l love you. Sophie
Please stay

912
01:29:41,643 --> 01:29:44,163
Il love you, too, Markl
Don't worry. I won't go

913
01:29:44,613 --> 01:29:45,783
Really!

914
01:29:46,882 --> 01:29:48,251
Are we a family?

915
01:29:48,583 --> 01:29:50,223
Yes, we're family

916
01:29:50,919 --> 01:29:52,229
Oh, good!

917
01:30:00,629 --> 01:30:02,969
I'll never let Suliman
get hold of Howl

918
01:30:20,248 --> 01:30:22,147
But the paper says we won

919
01:30:22,517 --> 01:30:25,007
Only fools swallow such lies

920
01:30:26,421 --> 01:30:29,581
How strange
l can't get Calcifer going

921
01:30:30,625 --> 01:30:32,265
Grandma, will you stop that?

922
01:30:32,661 --> 01:30:34,001
Such an awful stink

923
01:30:34,329 --> 01:30:36,959
Why deny an old lady her pleasures

924
01:30:37,966 --> 01:30:39,606
Open the window, Markl

925
01:30:43,672 --> 01:30:45,722
wouldn't open that now...

926
01:30:47,642 --> 01:30:51,742
In Calcifer's present state.
he can't possibly keep them out

927
01:30:54,282 --> 01:30:55,272
Markl!

928
01:31:06,161 --> 01:31:07,361
Close it quick!

929
01:31:14,035 --> 01:31:16,345
Look after Grandma, Markl
I'll check on the shop

930
01:31:35,523 --> 01:31:39,123
How dare you. now? If you've
energy to spare, put out the fires

931
01:32:04,019 --> 01:32:04,809
Howl!

932
01:32:18,600 --> 01:32:19,910
Dramatic as usual...

933
01:32:33,415 --> 01:32:34,175
Howl!

934
01:32:36,451 --> 01:32:38,531
I'm sorry
l had too many enemies, tonight

935
01:32:39,687 --> 01:32:42,147
Howl, oh, Howl

936
01:32:59,340 --> 01:33:01,240
Master Howl!
Sophie!

937
01:33:04,179 --> 01:33:06,869
Calcifer, be strong

938
01:33:11,986 --> 01:33:15,675
Madam, was that a gift
from Suliman?

939
01:33:16,591 --> 01:33:19,251
That granny fed me something nasty

940
01:33:20,228 --> 01:33:22,338
Why. if it isn't Howl

941
01:33:23,198 --> 01:33:26,418
I feel we need a nice long chat

942
01:33:27,469 --> 01:33:30,779
Likewise, Madam
But we've no time, now

943
01:33:31,840 --> 01:33:35,530
How unlike you
You're not running away

944
01:33:36,144 --> 01:33:37,604
Until later, then

945
01:33:38,713 --> 01:33:41,433
Stay here, Sophie
Calcifer will protect you

946
01:33:41,916 --> 01:33:43,586
I'll see to things outside

947
01:33:45,420 --> 01:33:46,620
Wait. Howl!

948
01:33:46,888 --> 01:33:49,198
Don't go! Please stay

949
01:33:49,991 --> 01:33:52,981
Another round of bombs is coming
Even Calcifer can't stop those

950
01:33:53,828 --> 01:33:55,498
Let's run away
Don't fight

951
01:33:56,164 --> 01:33:58,414
I'm through running away

952
01:33:59,367 --> 01:34:02,117
I've finally found someone
l want to protect...

953
01:34:02,604 --> 01:34:03,624
You

954
01:34:08,543 --> 01:34:09,442
Howl!

955
01:35:34,229 --> 01:35:35,459
That's our town

956
01:35:40,235 --> 01:35:41,255
There's Howl

957
01:35:50,945 --> 01:35:51,735
Howl!

958
01:36:01,789 --> 01:36:03,459
Sophie!
Turnip...

959
01:36:07,562 --> 01:36:09,052
Markl. come inside!

960
01:36:09,530 --> 01:36:12,110
Move? You're nuts
There's nothing there

961
01:36:12,634 --> 01:36:15,564
No, as long as we stay here,
Howl will keep fighting

962
01:36:16,371 --> 01:36:17,801
He's better off a coward

963
01:36:18,106 --> 01:36:19,476
Grandma, get up

964
01:36:19,807 --> 01:36:21,147
Going for a stroll?

965
01:36:21,709 --> 01:36:23,459
Suliman will find us, right away

966
01:36:23,978 --> 01:36:26,968
She already has. At this rate,
Howl will never make it back alive

967
01:36:27,482 --> 01:36:28,622
Sophie!

968
01:36:28,883 --> 01:36:30,053
The castle's falling apart

969
01:36:30,385 --> 01:36:32,225
That's all right
Markl, take Grandma

970
01:36:32,587 --> 01:36:33,457
Sure

971
01:36:35,857 --> 01:36:37,167
You. too, hop up now

972
01:36:37,725 --> 01:36:40,915
l can't! My contract says
l can't leave the fireplace

973
01:36:41,796 --> 01:36:44,046
If you two can't solve this.
I'll do it for you

974
01:36:44,599 --> 01:36:46,059
Watch it!

975
01:36:46,567 --> 01:36:48,437
Cut it out! Cut it out!

976
01:36:49,704 --> 01:36:51,603
If l leave, the house will collapse

977
01:36:51,973 --> 01:36:52,763
Fine!

978
01:36:56,744 --> 01:36:57,943
We're out

979
01:36:58,379 --> 01:37:00,129
I'd better go last

980
01:37:01,482 --> 01:37:04,322
Even I don't know what'll happen...

981
01:37:33,514 --> 01:37:35,504
I told you, it would collapse

982
01:37:35,883 --> 01:37:37,053
Rain!

983
01:37:39,821 --> 01:37:41,191
Is that heading for town?

984
01:37:41,489 --> 01:37:42,888
Look after Grandma, Markl

985
01:37:43,191 --> 01:37:44,891
Turnip, find us a way in

986
01:37:46,160 --> 01:37:48,269
Don't worry, Grandma
I'll take care of you

987
01:37:51,466 --> 01:37:53,396
Markl. we can get in here

988
01:38:03,411 --> 01:38:05,751
The roof's leaking
I'll go out

989
01:38:06,581 --> 01:38:07,721
Wait here

990
01:38:07,982 --> 01:38:10,032
It's wet, here...

991
01:38:16,057 --> 01:38:17,197
Hurry

992
01:38:19,527 --> 01:38:20,957
Too damp

993
01:38:24,799 --> 01:38:26,379
Bring Grandma here, Markl

994
01:38:26,934 --> 01:38:28,514
The castle's empty

995
01:38:29,036 --> 01:38:32,196
Il told you. if we'd stayed put,
Howl and ! could've handled it

996
01:38:34,776 --> 01:38:37,146
Calcifer, please
You're my last hope

997
01:38:38,079 --> 01:38:40,509
l want to go to Howl
Move the castle

998
01:38:41,983 --> 01:38:45,113
I know you can do it
You're so strong

999
01:38:45,987 --> 01:38:48,887
But there's no chimney here...

1000
01:38:49,524 --> 01:38:50,754
And the wood's damp...

1001
01:38:51,592 --> 01:38:55,402
As the saying goes, “The best
blaze brightest in adversity”

1002
01:38:56,030 --> 01:38:58,460
I've heard that, but...

1003
01:38:58,900 --> 01:38:59,950
You really think so?

1004
01:39:00,201 --> 01:39:01,901
You're so pretty, Cal

1005
01:39:02,236 --> 01:39:03,346
Sit here, Grandma

1006
01:39:03,971 --> 01:39:06,281
Then, give me something of yours,
Sophie

1007
01:39:06,841 --> 01:39:07,661
Of mine?

1008
01:39:07,875 --> 01:39:10,095
l can't do it alone
How about your eyes?

1009
01:39:10,511 --> 01:39:11,531
My eyes?

1010
01:39:11,946 --> 01:39:13,086
This?

1011
01:40:18,779 --> 01:40:21,119
Amazing, Calcifer!
You are the best!

1012
01:40:22,049 --> 01:40:24,449
Imagine what I could do with
your eyes and your heart

1013
01:40:24,952 --> 01:40:27,562
Heart! You have a heart?

1014
01:40:30,791 --> 01:40:32,221
Oh, my!

1015
01:40:44,839 --> 01:40:47,009
There's Howl
He's trapped

1016
01:40:52,680 --> 01:40:54,200
Hurry, Calcifer!

1017
01:40:55,049 --> 01:40:56,359
Don't!

1018
01:40:57,318 --> 01:40:58,188
Grandma!

1019
01:40:58,920 --> 01:41:00,060
Stop it!

1020
01:41:01,055 --> 01:41:02,785
Howl's heart

1021
01:41:04,292 --> 01:41:06,162
Cut it out!

1022
01:41:15,102 --> 01:41:15,972
Grandma!

1023
01:41:18,372 --> 01:41:19,952
It's hot, hot!

1024
01:41:20,641 --> 01:41:21,811
Let go!

1025
01:41:22,443 --> 01:41:23,813
You'll die, Grandma

1026
01:41:24,111 --> 01:41:26,010
No, it's mine!

1027
01:41:44,532 --> 01:41:45,872
Sophie!

1028
01:41:49,770 --> 01:41:50,880
Sophie!

1029
01:41:51,739 --> 01:41:54,669
She's so mean
That's mine

1030
01:42:38,386 --> 01:42:41,546
Oh, no. Heen. look what I've done
l poured water on Calcifer

1031
01:42:45,026 --> 01:42:47,516
What if I've killed Howl, too...

1032
01:43:14,388 --> 01:43:16,758
It's moving...
Is Howl alive?

1033
01:43:17,191 --> 01:43:18,861
Show me where he is

1034
01:43:40,848 --> 01:43:42,218
The castle door...

1035
01:45:00,694 --> 01:45:01,564
Heen...

1036
01:45:37,264 --> 01:45:38,084
Howl...

1037
01:45:56,851 --> 01:45:59,101
This must be Howl's childhood...

1038
01:47:18,499 --> 01:47:20,108
Howl!
Calcifer!

1039
01:47:22,436 --> 01:47:25,505
It's Sophie! Wait for me!
I promise I'll come back for you

1040
01:47:27,441 --> 01:47:29,191
Wait for me in the future!

1041
01:48:02,543 --> 01:48:05,093
I'll walk there
Heen, I'll walk

1042
01:48:05,846 --> 01:48:07,276
Il can't stop crying

1043
01:48:31,905 --> 01:48:33,105
Howl

1044
01:48:39,780 --> 01:48:42,360
I'm sorry ] took so long

1045
01:48:42,950 --> 01:48:45,320
You've been waiting all this time

1046
01:48:50,224 --> 01:48:52,564
Take me to Calcifer

1047
01:49:55,823 --> 01:49:56,723
Is he dead?

1048
01:49:56,957 --> 01:49:58,567
No, he's fine

1049
01:50:03,197 --> 01:50:04,367
Grandma...

1050
01:50:04,631 --> 01:50:07,821
Don't look at me
I don't have anything

1051
01:50:08,669 --> 01:50:09,539
Please

1052
01:50:12,072 --> 01:50:13,362
Grandma

1053
01:50:16,310 --> 01:50:18,560
You want it that badly?

1054
01:50:18,979 --> 01:50:19,999
Yes

1055
01:50:21,048 --> 01:50:24,617
Oh, well, in that case...
You'd better take good care of it

1056
01:50:25,586 --> 01:50:26,816
There

1057
01:50:28,222 --> 01:50:30,242
Thank you, Grandma

1058
01:50:46,607 --> 01:50:47,837
Calcifer

1059
01:50:49,209 --> 01:50:51,608
Sophie. ..
I'm all worn out

1060
01:50:52,045 --> 01:50:55,035
If l give Howl's heart back,
will it kill you?

1061
01:50:55,549 --> 01:50:57,769
Probably not, if you do it, Sophie

1062
01:50:58,819 --> 01:51:02,509
After all. we both survived
the water you dumped on me

1063
01:51:03,123 --> 01:51:04,433
I'd better try, then

1064
01:51:07,995 --> 01:51:10,894
It's all warm and fluttery
like a little bird

1065
01:51:11,398 --> 01:51:13,328
It's still only a child's heart

1066
01:51:14,568 --> 01:51:17,228
May Calcifer live a thousand years,

1067
01:51:17,704 --> 01:51:20,393
and may Howl recover his heart...

1068
01:51:32,586 --> 01:51:33,456
I'm alive!

1069
01:51:33,687 --> 01:51:35,087
I'm free!

1070
01:51:41,828 --> 01:51:43,528
He moved, he's alive!

1071
01:51:48,235 --> 01:51:49,844
You broke Calcifer's spell!

1072
01:52:04,985 --> 01:52:05,804
Turnip!

1073
01:52:18,999 --> 01:52:20,228
Turnip, are you OK?

1074
01:52:20,500 --> 01:52:22,230
I'll get you a new stick, right away

1075
01:52:25,105 --> 01:52:26,855
Thank you, Turnip

1076
01:52:35,082 --> 01:52:36,452
Thank you, Sophie

1077
01:52:37,751 --> 01:52:39,681
I'm a prince from the next kingdom

1078
01:52:40,053 --> 01:52:42,013
A cruel spell turned me
into a scarecrow

1079
01:52:42,522 --> 01:52:45,758
“beyond these tears”
A spell that only your beloved's
kiss could break

1080
01:52:45,759 --> 01:52:45,858
“beyond these tears”

1081
01:52:45,859 --> 01:52:48,894
“beyond these tears”
Exactly. And if Sophie hadn't saved me,
l would have died

1082
01:52:48,895 --> 01:52:50,325
Exactly. And if Sophie hadn't saved me,
l would have died

1083
01:52:50,831 --> 01:52:53,199
“my flickering smile”
My, you're good-looking

1084
01:52:53,200 --> 01:52:53,299
“my flickering smile”

